main event: A military report documented a sighting of an unidentified flying object in Dayton, Ohio, on 9 September 1965.
interesting points: The observation lasted around 20 minutes., The object was initially seen as a reflection in the windshield of a car., It was described as 'six feet in diameter' but appeared very distant and eventually diminished in size., The object was visible while driving towards town and was last seen parked at a local store., The report concluded the sighting was likely Venus due to its position in the sky.
sighted object: a bright object in the sky, initially perceived as a reflection
witness description: A military personnel who reported the sighting while driving.
